sql:
SELECT description
FROM data_sources
WHERE environment = 'production';

external_knowledge:
- Significant issues are those with more than 5 data points affected; 
- The production environment is typically where live applications are hosted and accessed by end-users; 
- High-severity alerts indicate critical issues that require immediate attention; 
- Performance data points are collected at specific timestamps and can be associated with various users and data sources.

sql:
SELECT AVG(latency_value) AS avg_latency
FROM latency_samples
WHERE environment = 'production';

SELECT MAX(latency_value) AS max_latency
FROM latency_samples
WHERE environment = 'production';

SELECT kpi_name
FROM kpi_settings
WHERE environment = 'production';

SELECT kpi_name, kpi_description
FROM kpi_settings
WHERE threshold > 10;
